                                                   May 1 digest                                         Sharath loses in 3rd round
    New Delhi: Sharath Kamal went down fighting to Gionis Panagiotis of Greece in a third round match to bring an end to Indias campaign at the World Table Tennis Championships at Yokohama on Friday. Sharath lost to Panagiotis 12-10, 9-11, 11-13, 13-11, 8-11, 8-11. Sharath later teamed up with Subhajit Saha and the duo went down 13-11, 7-11, 12-10, 5-11, 11-8, 9-11, 8-11 against Brazilian pair of Monteiro Thiago and Tsuboi Gustavo in a second round match.               
	United tour         
	Manchester: Manchester United will play in Indonesia for the first time since 1975 as part of the European champions off-season tour of Asia. The Red Devils will play an Indonesian Super League XI at Jakartas Gelora Bung Karno Stadium on July 20.               
	Adriano deal         
	Sao Paulo: Flamengo is close to signing World Cup striker Adriano, who deserted Inter Milan this month. The deal is 99 per cent complete, Flamengo president Delair Dumbrosck said on Thursday. We found a partner which will help pay for his salaries.               
	Odafe contract         
	 Panaji: Okolie Odafe renewed his contract with Churchill Brothers Friday for a huge amount. Odafe along with strike partner Felix Chimaokwu inked the deal thus ending speculation that the Nigerian would sign for East Bengal. Gourmangi Singh also had a tempting offer from East Bengal but finally settled for Churchill Brothers.               
	Girls soccer         
	New Delhi: India opened their campaign in the AFC U-14 Girls Football Festival with victories against Bhutan and Iran. In the tournament being held in Colombo for South and Central Asian countries, Indian girls walloped Bhutan 9-0 and then defeated Iran 3-1.         
